  🔠 call_rixng6gi | Return # Solid State Batteries: Status Report (Late 2024 - 2025)
     
     ## Executive Summary
     
     Solid-state batteries (SSBs) represent the next generation of lithium-based battery technology, replacing the flammable liquid electrolyte in conventional lithium-ion batteries with a solid material. While significant progress has been made, **no mass-market consumer vehicles with solid-state batteries are yet available in late 2024/2025**. The technology remains in the demonstration, prototyping, and pilot production phase, with most automakers targeting commercial production between 2026 and 2030.
     
     ---
     
     ## 1. Market Launch Timeline: When Are They Hitting the Market?
     
     ### Current Status (Late 2024 - Early 2025)
     - **No mass-market consumer EVs** feature solid-state batteries as of early 2025
     - **Demonstration vehicles and prototypes** are being tested on public roads
     
     ### Demonstration and Prototype Vehicles
     
     | Company | Vehicle | Status | Timeline |
     |---------|---------|--------|----------|
     | **Mercedes-Benz** | Modified EQS | Road tests with lithium-metal SSB | End of 2024 (integrated), road tests starting 2025 |
     | **Rimac Technology** | Concept vehicle | Unveiled at IAA Mobility 2025 | September 2025 |
     | **Stellantis + Factorial Energy** | Dodge Charger Daytona EVs | Integration testing | 2026 (planned) |
     | **BMW + Solid Power** | i7 mule | Testing sulfide-based electrolyte | 2025 (demonstration vehicles planned) |
     
     ###量产 Production Timelines (Mass Market)
     
     | Company | Target Timeline | Key Details |
     |---------|-----------------|-------------|
     | **Honda** | March 2025 | Production process launch; demonstration line started early 2024 |
     | **Nissan** | 2028 | EV launch with all-solid-state batteries; 65% cost reduction target |
     | **Toyota** | 2027-2028 | Mass production; 750-mile range, 10-80% charge in 10 minutes |
     | **Nissan + Panasonic + SK** | 2029 | Joint development target |
     | **QuantumScape (VW-backed)** | 2025-2026 | 24-layer prototype cells delivered in 2024 |
     | **SAIC Motor** | 2026 | Mass production of second-generation SSBs |
     | **BMW** | 2025-2026 | Demonstration vehicles first, then mass production |
     
     **Conclusion**: While demonstration vehicles are being road-tested in late 2024/2025, **widespread availability in consumer vehicles is expected between 2026 and 2030**, with most major automakers targeting the second half of the decade.
     
     ---
     
     ## 2. Major Companies Involved
     
     ### Automakers (OEMs)
     
